text: The 1905 Tempe Normal Owls football team was an American football team that represented Tempe Normal School (later renamed Arizona State University) as an independent during the 1905 college football season. In their seventh season under head coach Frederick M. Irish, the Owls compiled a 0–3 record and were outscored by their opponents by a combined total of 28 to 8. The team lost games to the Phoenix Indian School (8–17), Phoenix High School (0–5), and Tempe High School (0–6). ==References== Tempe Normal Category:Arizona State Sun Devils football seasons Category:College football winless seasons Category:1905 in Arizona Territory
